13:
He foolishly gave into his emotions
and lost his life for it... In the end, he
too was only human.
22:
Fine. Guess I'll have to knock some
sense into you!
27:
I see your power output has
increased.
46: Don't you DARE look down on me!
52:
Give up. Even if you are able to take
me down, it won't mean anything.
54:
The heroes' pain, their suffering, their
anxieties... None of them have any
meaning!
57:
They do nothing to change the
world!
60:
The former troubleshooters continue
their attack on the city...
62:
It's hard to believe that we once
considered these people heroes.
Clearly these brutes only know how
to speak with their fists.
64:
Heroes, huh? Sounds like just
another problem left to us by the
previous generation.
67:
Time to face reality, you little
wannabe... Surely you see who is in
the wrong here.
71: Heh... Yeah, people sure are stupid.
79: I mean, it's pretty funny, right?
82:
No matter how bad they come off,
everyone's just fighting for their
version of justice.
86:
No matter how ordinary someone is,
they've still got justice in their hearts.
Isn't that right?
90:
No. What you saw is the definition of
mob mentality! These people are
nothing but sheep!
98:
Enough of your idealistic drivel. I'll
blow it all away!
132:
How could you?! She was trying to
save someone!
149:
Look, I KNOW you didn't become
strong just to cut down people you
think deserve it!
152:
The Themis I knew fought to SAVE
people!
156:
So what about you?! Why are you a
hero?!
165:
Hostile activity detected. Themis,
initiate termination.
173:
Subject unable to continue
combat.
Removing admin status and forcing
shut down of subject ID: LCP001.
175:
Third-party operation disabled.
Assuming independent operations...
Commencing arrest of hostiles.
182:
I don't know why you're so mad at
me...
185:
But I hate you. I used to look up to
you... You were so strong, so
steadfast... The kind of hero I wanted
to be.
187:
Yet despite all that, you let yourself
go all grimdark, and now you're
blinded by those feelings. I hate you
for that.
191:
You clawed your way to the top, but
now what?! Sure, being the best of
the best comes with its fair share of
burdens...
194:
But that just proves how strong
those at the top are! How prepared
they are to face any and all
adversity! I KNOW you have what it
takes.
198:
Now get up, hero... I won't let you
throw it all away like this!
203: Is this... how you felt all along?
207:
Are you two unharmed? Everything
going according to plan?
216:
Bad news, kids. The machines are
starting to run wild. They can no
longer distinguish friend from foe.
219:
Dismantling the AI is proceeding as
planned, but it may try to escape
into a local server in your area!
234:
If it isn't the town hero. Well? Still
feeling down in the dumps? Or are
you ready to leave your despair
behind?
242:
If you are, perhaps a chat with our
engineer is in order?
